    {
      "number": 5,
      "id": "PR_kwDOTI8nP87x2Fw6",
      "title": "Expand dbv to also have dbv1 and dbvm",
      "url": "https://github.com/skyfire-xyz/draft-skyfire-oauth-id-verification/pull/5",
      "state": "MERGED",
      "author": "selfissued",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "Database verification from a single database has different compliance properties than database verification from multiple databases, as pointed out by @experian-nashali.  Added the `dbv1` (one database) and `dbvm` (multiple databases) methods to enable this distinction to be made.\r\n\r\nNote that keeping `dbv` with an unspecified number of databases parallels the relationship between `pop`, `swk`, and `hwk`.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
      "createdAt": "2026-07-15T03:24:38Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-07-15T16:13:19Z",
      "baseRepository": "skyfire-xyz/draft-skyfire-oauth-id-verification",
